CatDescriptText: Mr. Henry Turner, 2935 Mulberry Way, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 23, 1957, pg. 10 with question: "Do you think Negroes in Pittsburgh use their economic power wisely?" answer reads: "Some Negroes do, and others don't. I would say that the majority of them don't."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Henry Turner wearing moustache, light colored hat, and dark zippered jacket, leaning on metal wall
